	Bugfix in test `startlabel-default.test'
	* tests/startlabel-default.test (call to `$EGREP -v'): Bugfix: we
	forgot to put the file to grep on the command line:
	  (-) old command:  $EGREP -v '...' && TESTCASE-FAILURE
	  (+) new command:  $EGREP -v '...' FILE && TESTCASE-FAILURE
	It's important to note that the old call to egrep always failed, since
	we close standard input of test scripts in `testlib.sh'; thus we could
	have a false negative in this test script (BAD!)

